This paper proposes a novel ranking approach for identifying discrepancies between preliminary and final versions of medical reports. The approach involves analyzing textual and ontological overlaps between the two versions. This work involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the use of ontologies suggests a potential connection to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) are also relevant sub-categories given the focus on ranking and learning from discrepancies in the reports.
